            <bug_when>2013-12-09 13:54:05 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>If a running animation is stopped, no animationEnd will be fired. This can cause unexpected behavior, particularly if stop() is called by the AnimationHandle, e.g. if a new animation is started. We should find out if this behavior is covered by the specification and, if not, whether we should manually fire the animationEnd.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
